    "title": "HEIRLOOM CLIENT INTAKE – HIGH TIER ONLY (Nuclear Version)",
    "summary": "**For:** Fuck You Level and Fuck Em All (Nuclear) vaults only.",
    "content": "# HEIRLOOM CLIENT INTAKE – HIGH TIER ONLY (Nuclear Version)\n\n**For:** Fuck You Level and Fuck Em All (Nuclear) vaults only.  \n**Location:** `docs/HEIRLOOM-INTAKE-QUESTIONNAIRE.md` (also copied to `heirloom/intake-questionnaire.md`)  \n**Purpose:** Extremely invasive, based, truth-serum onboarding that feeds the per-bloodline Heirloom instance. Answers are stored **client-side encrypted** (AES-256-GCM) in the vault manifest only. Heirloom never sees them until unlocked by the owner's passphrase or valid 5-Proof release.\n\n**Georgia Note (always surface):** All answers are captured under Georgia RUFADAA digital asset framework at 5655 Peachtree Parkway, Norcross, GA 30092. These instructions are designed to be cryptographically verifiable and to help families avoid 18+ month Georgia probate.\n\n---\n\n## Section 1: Family Truth Serum (Heir Trust Map)\n\n1. Rank every potential heir / beneficiary from **most trusted** to **most likely to fuck you over** (include names, relationships, and one-sentence reason).\n2. Which family member(s) would you happily disown today if it were socially acceptable? Why?\n3. Any secret children, hidden relationships, or undisclosed family you need the vault to acknowledge or actively conceal?\n4. Who should get **nothing** but will cry the loudest and/or litigate the hardest?\n5. Who in the family already knows (or suspects) about the vault? How much do they know?\n6. Are there any \"family secrets\" (affairs, crimes, addictions, medical) that should be released only under specific conditions or never released?\n\n---\n\n## Section 2: Death & Incapacity Scenarios (Different Protocols per Tier)\n\n1. Natural death vs. suspicious / violent death — do you want **completely different** release instructions, beneficiaries, or \"burn\" triggers?\n2. If you are **murdered**, what should happen? (Immediate full release? Slow leak to law enforcement + media? Burn certain chains? Specific \"Fuck You\" actions against named parties?)\n3. If you are **incapacitated but not legally dead** (coma, dementia, stroke), what should the vault and Heirloom do? (Guardians take over? Time-locked partial release? Full lock + legal defense mode?)\n4. \"If I go missing\" slow-leak protocol: after how many days/weeks of no check-in should non-sensitive inventory + instructions begin leaking to designated parties?\n5. \"If I die under suspicious circumstances\" protocol: which documents, hashes, or full bundles should auto-release to media, law enforcement, specific attorneys, or on-chain transparency logs? Include any pre-written statements.\n\n---\n\n## Section 3: Psychotic Controls & Kill Switches (Fuck You / Nuclear Only)\n\n1. Do you want a **\"Fuck You\" button** (or oracle-triggered) that can burn, redirect, or lock assets if forced access, subpoena, or key compromise is detected? Which assets? To where (DAO, charity, specific wallets, black hole)?\n2. Should certain assets or document bundles only unlock if specific heirs hit life milestones (age, marriage, sobriety, criminal record clean, business success, etc.)? Detail the conditions.\n3. Do you want Heirloom to **actively fight** the government, ex-spouse, creditors, or hostile family members (legal templates, on-chain challenges, media packets, attorney coordination)?\n4. Plausible deniability architecture: describe how you want the master recovery material sharded so that even **you** (post-setup) do not hold enough to unilaterally move everything without quorum or time-lock.\n5. Multi-jurisdiction / offshore / DAO layer: list any specific trusts, foundations, DAOs, or foreign entities that should receive redirects or be named in policies.\n6. Biometric + geographic + time-based triggers: any specific phone, face, location, or calendar conditions that should arm/disarm release or burn paths? (These live only in client-side encrypted config.)\n\n---\n\n## Section 4: Legacy Tone & Final Messages (Heirloom Personality)\n\n1. What tone should Heirloom use when speaking to your children / heirs? (Loving but firm / Cold and clinical / Based and savage / Terrifying and ominous / Custom — write the voice)\n2. Any specific lessons, warnings, or final messages you want **burned into the AI** so they are delivered in your exact voice/style even decades later?\n3. For generational (Nuclear): what should the 100+ year tutor mode teach the bloodline about money, power, family loyalty, and sovereignty?\n4. Any pre-written video / audio / text messages (CIDs) that should be attached to specific heirs or scenarios?\n5. Attorney / executor / guardian coordination: list the real humans (with DIDs if known) who get white-glove or elevated access, and any special instructions for them.\n\n---\n\n## Submission & Storage Rules\n\n- All answers are **client-encrypted before leaving the browser**.\n- They become part of the encrypted vault manifest + special \"heirloom_context\" blob (CID + contentHash + ZK commitment).\n- Heirloom instance (when invoked) receives only the decrypted context the current proof level allows.\n- Changes to answers require owner re-encryption + new manifest version + optional on-chain anchor.\n- For Nuclear tier: you may run multiple isolated Heirloom instances (one per major asset class or jurisdiction) with different subsets of this intake.\n\n**Owner signature / date line at end of intake (client-side only).**\n\nThis is not therapy. This is war planning for your bloodline's survival after you are gone.\n\n---\n\n**Next:** After intake, the tiered Heirloom power level is activated in your vault entitlement. See `heirloom/tiers/` and `heirloom/kernel.md`."
